    "name": "Shochikubai Hostel No.3 - Men Only",
    "detail": "Yes, for those complaining about the late check-in (5-11PM only) and early check-out (9AM), no food services, smoking area every floor, shower schedules, etc, be informed that this is basically a salaryman's budget hostel and as such caters to their needs first of all rather than those of leisure travelers. For the price, (especially for walk-ins at only 1500yen/night versus around 2300yen here in Agoda) this is an exceptional deal being close to Nagoya Station. (10-min walk) You get your own private room with centralized AC, fan, TV, 1 set of towel, toothbrush/toothpaste and slippers per night of stay. There's a vending machine at the reception area but if that's not enough, you can just walk outside and you'd see one in just every corner plus a convenience store a 5-min walk away in every direction. Overall satisfied and will stay here again if I'm back in Nagoya.",
